課程概述 Course Description
 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    In fiscal year 2004, the US National Institute of Health launched the NIH Roadmap which aimed at “New Pathways to Discovery”, “Research Teams of the Future”, and “Reengineering the Clinical Research Enterprise”, opening a new era for translational biomedical research. The goal of this course is to introduce students to fundamental knowledge and technological approaches for translating biomedical research into clinically applicable therapies. The course will start with an introduction of effective scientific communication covering oral presentation and proposal writing, followed with lectures by the faculty experienced in translational research.    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1呂佩融--Introduction2莊偉哲--Design of Selective and Potent Integrin Drugs3謝奇璋--From primary immunodeficiency to redox regulation4張南山--Role of WWOX in tumor suppression and neurodegeneration 5謝達斌--Nano medicine6沈孟儒--Calcium signaling as a potential target for cancer treatment.7吳華林--Thrombomodulin8陳鈴津--Rationals and strategies for glycan-targeted cancer immunotherapy.9Michael Hughes--The iWRR: biomedical research projects for novel therapies of tissue regeneration.10張明熙--New drug development targeting proinflammatory cytokine11沈延盛--The significance of tumor associated macrophages in cancer.12Marcus J. Calkins--Activating endogenous neuroprotective pathways to slow or halt progression of neurodegenerative disease.13劉秉彥--ROCK and Rho in Cardiometabolic Translational Medicine.14蕭宏昇--組織微陣列建立與新藥開發(Academia Sinica)15黃奇英-- Drug repurposing16王照元-- Pharmacogenetic Research and Clinical Implications in Colorectal Cancer17呂佩融--TBD18期末考 

